verbose_text: The phosphorescence signal of the ligand fod (at 500 nm) could not be observed in the phosphorescence spectrum of [Eu (fod) 3 dpbt] upon the excitation at 416 nm, which was in consistent with the fact that the energy level of T 1 (fod) was higher than that of T 1 (dpbt) by 806 cm -1, indicating that the energy migration process T 1 (dpbt)--> T 1 (fod) hardly happened in [Eu (fod) 3 dpbt].
